  <thing id="rauDrdBKBD" name="Blood Drain" description="Any living creature damaged by a blood knight&apos;s natural attack takes 2 points of Constitution damage in addition to the normal damage. This Constitution damage is subject to the multiplier for a critical hit, just as normal damage would be. In a grapple, a blood knight deals 1d4 points of Constitution damage to a living foe each round that the grapple is maintained. On each such successful attack, the blood knight gains 5 temporary hit points." compset="RaceSpec">
